# Laravel Accelerator

This is the `Laravel/` accelerator folder, shipping a skill-based workflow specialized for Laravel (Composer + Artisan + Eloquent). The framework-agnostic native-PHP base lives in the sibling `PHP Core/` folder; other frameworks (Symfony, etc.) get their own sibling folder.

## Command -> Agent -> Skill

- **Commands** (`.cursor/commands/*.md`) are `/slash` entry points; invoke with `/name` and pass context as `$ARGUMENTS`.
- **Agents** (`.cursor/agents/*.md`) run one skill in an isolated context, then stop.
- **Skills** (`.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`) contain the actual workflow.

Execute only the selected skill, then stop. Do not auto-chain. Always end with a Context Summary and Next Steps.

## Typical Flow

`brainstorm` -> `requirements-analyst` -> `architect` -> `api-designer` -> `writing-plans` -> `architecture-implementer` -> `coder` / `coder-frontend` / `filament` / `eloquent` / `queues-jobs` / `events-notifications` / `auth-scaffolding` / `caching` / `console-scheduler` / `file-storage` / `package-developer` -> `test-generator` -> `code-reviewer` / `security-reviewer` -> `verify` -> `finishing-branch` / `release`

Support skills: `researcher`, `council`, `database-designer`, `dependency-manager`, `refactorer`, `performance-optimization`, `systematic-debugger`, `documentation-generator`, `review-pr`, `reflect`, `memory-bank`.

## Sources Of Truth

Enforcement (`.cursor/hooks`) > Policy (`AGENTS.md`) > Architecture/runtime truth (`specs/`, code, config, migrations, tests) > Verified memory (`memory-bank/`) > Skills (`.cursor/skills/`) > Examples > Docs. See `.cursor/DOD.md` and `.cursor/GOLDEN-PRINCIPLES.md`.
